<p>Calls to client workflow hooks, where workflow validation and bespoke changes can be carried out, have been added to the system. This should not change any functionality if the client hooks do not exist.<br />
<br />
They are used when updating statuses of multiple items, getting status dropdowns in editor screens and saving items.<br />
<br />
Implementation:<br />
<br />
1) This change has been made for Promos, Funds, ROBs and ROB Groups (Contracts and Material Terms), with each type calling one client hook:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Promos:</strong> APP_Procast_SP_PROMO_SHARED_Workflow_HOOK</li>
    <li><strong>Funds:</strong>&nbsp;APP_Procast_SP_FUND_SHARED_Workflow_HOOK</li>
    <li><strong>ROBs:</strong> APP_Procast_SP_ROB_SHARED_Workflow_HOOK</li>
    <li><strong>ROB Groups:</strong> APP_Procast_SP_ROBGROUP_SHARED_Workflow_HOOK</li>
</ul>
<p><img alt="" src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">2) The Workflow Hooks are passed </span><strong style="line-height: 1.42857;">@IsValidation</strong><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"> and </span><strong style="line-height: 1.42857;">@IsSave</strong><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"> flags to determine if they should validate workflow or carry out any&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 20px;">additional</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">&nbsp;bespoke&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 20px;">functionality</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">.</span></p>
<p>They work by updating #tmpWorkflowValidationTable, which takes its structure from the newly created table type app.WorkflowValidationTableType, and by then carrying out any other changes.<br />
